Theme: Moral "truth" through naturalism
Time Period: Early Renaissance
Artwork: Masaccio, The Tribute Money
Medium: Fresco painting
Prompt: Create a painting to go on a wall. Use natural colors on wet plaster. Show a group of people standing in an outdoor space with mountains and buildings behind them. Use linear perspective so the background looks like it goes back into the distance. The people should have realistic bodies and small shadows that make them look 3D. The light should come from one direction, like the sun. The scene should feel calm and peaceful.
Purpose: This artwork shows the new ideas of the Early Renaissance, when artists focused on realism and real human emotion. People were starting to study perspective to make paintings look more believable. Artists also cared about showing real human experiences. This kind of artwork was meant to help people understand religious stories by making them look like they were happening in real life.
